<html>
<head>
<title>Internal CSS</title>
<style>
    body {
        background-color: #e8f4f8;
        font-family: Tahoma;
        margin: 40px;
    }
    h1 {
        color: darkgreen;
        text-align: center;
        border-bottom: 2px solid darkgreen;
        padding-bottom: 10px;
    }
    p {
        color: #444;
        font-size: 17px;
        line-height: 1.8;
    }
    .box {
        background-color: white;
        border: 1px solid #ccc;
        padding: 20px;
        border-radius: 8px;
        width: 400px;
    }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<h1>Internal CSS Example</h1>
<div class="box">
<p>This page is styled using internal CSS written inside the style tag in the head section.</p>
<p>Internal CSS applies only to the current HTML page.</p>
</div>
</body>
</html>
